# DTO (Data Transfer Object) Patterns
## 📌 OVERVIEW

DTOs define how data moves between client and server.

### PURPOSE

* Define API request/response structure
* Validate incoming data
* Hide internal entity structure
* Control exposed fields

---

## 📂 DTO STRUCTURE

### DO

* Place DTOs under:

```id="k1m8fz"
dto/
  ├── request/
  ├── response/
```

---

## 🟢 REQUEST DTO RULES

### DO

* Use for all incoming API data
* Apply validation annotations:

  * `@NotNull`
  * `@NotBlank`
  * `@Size`
* Keep only required fields

### EXAMPLE

```java
public class CreateTaskRequest {

    @NotBlank
    private String title;

    private String description;
}
```

---

## 🔵 RESPONSE DTO RULES

### DO

* Use for all API responses
* Return only required fields
* Include identifiers and status

### DO NOT

* Do not expose internal entity fields

### EXAMPLE

```java
public class TaskResponse {

    private Long id;
    private String title;
    private String status;
}
```

---

## ⚠️ ENTITY VS DTO

### DO

* Convert Entity → Response DTO
* Convert Request DTO → Entity

### DO NOT

* Do not expose Entity directly in controller

---

## 🔄 MAPPING RULES

### DO

* Map DTOs in service layer
* Use manual mapping or mapper class

### EXAMPLE

```java
Task task = new Task();
task.setTitle(request.getTitle());

TaskResponse response = new TaskResponse();
response.setId(task.getId());
```

---

## 🔁 UPDATE DTO (PARTIAL)

### DO

* Use optional fields for updates

### EXAMPLE

```java
public class UpdateTaskRequest {

    private String title;
    private String description;
}
```

---

## 🧾 VALIDATION RULES

### DO

* Validate all request DTOs
* Use `@Valid` in controller

### EXAMPLE

```java
@PostMapping
public ResponseEntity<TaskResponse> create(@Valid @RequestBody CreateTaskRequest request) {
```

---

## 🧱 NESTED DTOS

### DO

* Use nested DTOs only when required
* Keep structure simple

### DO NOT

* Avoid deep nesting

---

## 📊 PAGINATION DTO

### DO

* Use standard pagination request

### EXAMPLE

```java
public class PaginationRequest {
    private int page = 1;
    private int limit = 10;
}
```

---

## 🚫 DO NOT RULES

* Do not use Entity in API
* Do not add business logic in DTO
* Do not use `Map<String, Object>`
* Do not expose sensitive fields

---

## ⚙️ BEST PRACTICES

### DO

* Keep DTOs small and focused
* Use separate DTOs for request and response
* Keep naming consistent:

  * `CreateTaskRequest`
  * `TaskResponse`

### DO NOT

* Do not reuse same DTO for request and response

---

## 🧠 AI ENFORCEMENT RULES

* MUST use DTOs for all APIs
* MUST validate request DTOs
* MUST NOT expose entities
* MUST separate request and response DTOs
* MUST map DTOs in service layer

